# General Conventions

> Project-wide conventions for {{ project_name | default("this project") }}.

## Naming

- Files: `{{ file_naming | default("kebab-case") }}`
- Directories: `{{ dir_naming | default("kebab-case") }}`
- ICM documents: `XX-name` prefix for ordered items (stages, refs, patterns)

## Documentation

- Every significant directory MUST have a `CLAUDE.md` and `CONTEXT.md` pair
- `CLAUDE.md` describes what IS in the directory (static)
- `CONTEXT.md` describes what is HAPPENING (dynamic, session-scoped)
- L3b+ documents MUST have YAML frontmatter with: title, layer, classification
- Hot-path documents (L0, L1, Distributed) use `<!-- prism:managed -->` markers only

## Code Style

{% if code_style %}{{ code_style }}{% else %}- Follow language-specific conventions
- Prefer clarity over brevity
- Keep functions focused and testable
{% endif %}

## Git

- Commit messages: `type: description` (feat, fix, refactor, test, chore, docs)
- Branch naming: `feature/description`, `fix/description`
- No force-pushing to main/develop

## PRISM Integration

- Run `/prism:status` to check project health
- Drift is auto-detected and fixed at session start
- Decisions are auto-logged from conversation
- Stage transitions are managed automatically via hooks
